{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887718907,"sessionID":"ses_284d83369ffeu6xf7SuTZDf0Mj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2814c7001fUidz6gVikJOJE","messageID":"msg_d7b2801ec0015zcoXX5uD4g94z","sessionID":"ses_284d83369ffeu6xf7SuTZDf0Mj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_39a0bf9ae94b42cea0735746","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 本提案实现 AgentCube Python SDK 的 PCAP 分析器示例应用，展示如何使用 `CodeInterpreterClient` 在沙箱中执行网络数据包分析任务。该示例是 AgentCube SDK 的官方示例应用，帮助用户理解如何使用 Code Interpreter 进行文件处理、代码执行和结果获取。\n6: \n7: 目标是：\n8: \n9: 1. **SDK 使用示范** - 展示 `CodeInterpreterClient` 的完整使用流程\n10: 2. **PCAP 分析场景** - 演示如何上传、解析、分析网络数据包文件\n11: 3. **最佳实践** - 提供文件操作、代码执行、错误处理的最佳实践示例\n12: 4. **可运行示例** - 提供完整的、可独立运行的示例代码和测试数据\n13: \n14: 本提案基于 Python SDK design.md 和 spec.md 实现，遵循 AgentCube 示例应用规范。\n15: \n16: ## Scope\n17: \n18: **Module:** example  \n19: **Language:** Python  \n20: **Size:** M\n21: \n22: 本 AR 包含：\n23: \n24: - **包含内容：**\n25:   - `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/` - PCAP 分析器示例目录\n26:     - `README.md` - 示例说明文档\n27:     - `pcap_analyzer.py` - 主示例脚本\n28:     - `sample_pcap.py` - 生成示例 PCAP 文件的脚本\n29:     - `requirements.txt` - 示例依赖\n30:   - `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/test_pcaps/` - 示例 PCAP 文件目录\n31:     - `basic_http.pcap` - 基础 HTTP 流量示例\n32:     - `dns_queries.pcap` - DNS 查询示例\n33:   - 相关单元测试和验证脚本\n34: \n35: - **不包含内容：**\n36:   - SDK 核心代码修改（由 AR-028/AR-029 管理）\n37:   - PCAP 解析库开发（使用现有 `scapy` 库）\n38:   - 服务端代码修改\n39:   - 文档站点更新（由文档团队管理）\n40: \n41: ## Current State Analysis\n42: \n43: ### 现有示例状态\n44: \n45: 根据 `sdk-python/examples/` 目录检查：\n46: - 现有示例：`basic_usage.py`, `agent_runtime_usage.py`\n47: - 无 PCAP 分析相关示例\n48: - 无文件上传/下载完整流程示例\n49: \n50: ### 参考设计规范\n51: \n52: 根据 `python-sdk/design.md` 和 `python-sdk/spec.md`：\n53: \n54: **`CodeInterpreterClient` API：**\n55: ```python\n56: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n57:     def __init__(\n58:         self,\n59:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n60:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n61:         ttl: int = 3600,\n62:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n63:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n64:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n65:         verbose: bool = False,\n66:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n67:     )\n68: \n69:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n70:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n71:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n72:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n73:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None\n74:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\")\n75: ```\n76: \n77: **环境要求：**\n78: - Python >= 3.10\n79: - 依赖：`requests`, `PyJWT`, `cryptography`\n80: - 示例依赖：`scapy` (PCAP 解析)\n81: \n82: ### 差距分析\n83: \n84: 1. **缺少复杂示例** - 现有示例仅展示基础用法，缺少复杂场景\n85: 2. **缺少文件操作示例** - 无完整的文件上传/处理/下载流程\n86: 3. **缺少第三方库使用示例** - 无展示如何在沙箱中安装和使用第三方库的示例\n87: 4. **缺少错误处理示例** - 无展示如何处理常见错误的示例\n88: \n89: ### 示例特殊需求\n90: \n91: 根据 AgentCube 示例规范：\n92: \n93: 1. **独立可运行** - 示例应可独立运行，不依赖其他示例\n94: 2. **文档完整** - 每个示例需包含 README 说明\n95: 3. **环境隔离** - 示例应有独立的依赖配置\n96: 4. **测试数据** - 提供测试数据或生成脚本\n97: 5. **错误处理** - 展示完整的错误处理和日志记录\n98: \n99: ## Proposed Changes\n100: \n101: ### 1. 目录结构\n102: \n103: ```\n104: sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/\n105: ├── README.md                      # 示例说明文档\n106: ├── pcap_analyzer.py               # 主示例脚本\n107: ├── sample_pcap.py                 # 生成示例 PCAP 文件\n108: ├── requirements.txt               # 示例依赖\n109: └── test_pcaps/\n110:     ├── basic_http.pcap            # HTTP 流量示例\n111:     └── dns_queries.pcap           # DNS 查询示例\n112: ```\n113: \n114: ### 2. 示例依赖 (requirements.txt)\n115: \n116: ```txt\n117: # PCAP 分析器示例依赖\n118: scapy>=2.5.0\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### 3. PCAP 生成脚本 (sample_pcap.py)\n122: \n123: ```python\n124: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n125: \"\"\"Generate sample PCAP files for testing the PCAP analyzer example.\"\"\"\n126: \n127: from scapy.all import (\n128:     Ether,\n129:     IP,\n130:     TCP,\n131:     UDP,\n132:     DNS,\n133:     DNSQR,\n134:     Raw,\n135:     wrpcap,\n136: )\n137: from pathlib import Path\n138: \n139: \n140: def create_basic_http_pcap(output_path: str) -> None:\n141:     \"\"\"Create a sample PCAP with basic HTTP traffic.\"\"\"\n142:     packets = []\n143:     \n144:     # HTTP GET request\n145:     http_get = (\n146:         Ether() /\n147:         IP(src=\"192.168.1.100\", dst=\"93.184.216.34\") /\n148:         TCP(sport=54321, dport=80, flags=\"PA\") /\n149:         Raw(load=b\"GET /index.html HTTP/1.1\\r\\nHost: example.com\\r\\n\\r\\n\")\n150:     )\n151:     packets.append(http_get)\n152:     \n153:     # HTTP response\n154:     http_response = (\n155:         Ether() /\n156:         IP(src=\"93.184.216.34\", dst=\"192.168.1.100\") /\n157:         TCP(sport=80, dport=54321, flags=\"PA\") /\n158:         Raw(\n159:             load=b\"HTTP/1.1 200 OK\\r\\nContent-Type: text/html\\r\\n\\r\\n\"\n160:             b\"<html><body>Hello World</body></html>\"\n161:         )\n162:     )\n163:     packets.append(http_response)\n164:     \n165:     wrpcap(output_path, packets)\n166:     print(f\"Created {output_path} with {len(packets)} packets\")\n167: \n168: \n169: def create_dns_queries_pcap(output_path: str) -> None:\n170:     \"\"\"Create a sample PCAP with DNS queries.\"\"\"\n171:     packets = []\n172:     \n173:     # DNS query for example.com\n174:     dns_query = (\n175:         Ether() /\n176:         IP(src=\"192.168.1.100\", dst=\"8.8.8.8\") /\n177:         UDP(sport=12345, dport=53) /\n178:         DNS(rd=1, qd=DNSQR(qname=\"example.com\"))\n179:     )\n180:     packets.append(dns_query)\n181:     \n182:     # DNS response\n183:     dns_response = (\n184:         Ether() /\n185:         IP(src=\"8.8.8.8\", dst=\"192.168.1.100\") /\n186:         UDP(sport=53, dport=12345) /\n187:         DNS(\n188:             id=dns_query[DNS].id,\n189:             qr=1,\n190:             aa=0,\n191:             rd=1,\n192:             ra=1,\n193:             qd=dns_query[DNS].qd,\n194:             an=DNSRR(rrname=\"example.com\", rdata=\"93.184.216.34\"),\n195:         )\n196:     )\n197:     packets.append(dns_response)\n198:     \n199:     # DNS query for google.com\n200:     dns_query2 = (\n201:         Ether() /\n202:         IP(src=\"192.168.1.100\", dst=\"8.8.8.8\") /\n203:         UDP(sport=12346, dport=53) /\n204:         DNS(rd=1, qd=DNSQR(qname=\"google.com\"))\n205:     )\n206:     packets.append(dns_query2)\n207:     \n208:     wrpcap(output_path, packets)\n209:     print(f\"Created {output_path} with {len(packets)} packets\")\n210: \n211: \n212: def main() -> None:\n213:     \"\"\"Generate all sample PCAP files.\"\"\"\n214:     output_dir = Path(__file__).parent / \"test_pcaps\"\n215:     output_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n216:     \n217:     create_basic_http_pcap(str(output_dir / \"basic_http.pcap\"))\n218:     create_dns_queries_pcap(str(output_dir / \"dns_queries.pcap\"))\n219:     \n220:     print(f\"\\nSample PCAP files created in {output_dir}\")\n221: \n222: \n223: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n224:     main()\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### 4. 主示例脚本 (pcap_analyzer.py)\n228: \n229: ```python\n230: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n231: \"\"\"\n232: PCAP Analyzer Example for AgentCube Python SDK.\n233: \n234: This example demonstrates how to use the CodeInterpreterClient to:\n235: 1. Upload PCAP files to the sandbox\n236: 2. Install dependencies (scapy) in the sandbox\n237: 3. Analyze network traffic using Python code\n238: 4. Download analysis results\n239: \n240: Prerequisites:\n241:     - ROUTER_URL environment variable set\n242:     - WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable (optional)\n243:     - Auth token file or token (optional, for K8s SA auth)\n244: \n245: Usage:\n246:     python pcap_analyzer.py [pcap_file]\n247: \"\"\"\n248: \n249: import os\n250: import sys\n251: import json\n252: import base64\n253: import logging\n254: from pathlib import Path\n255: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any, List\n256: \n257: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n258: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError, DataPlaneError\n259: \n260: \n261: # Configure logging\n262: logging.basicConfig(\n263:     level=logging.INFO,\n264:     format=\"%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s\",\n265: )\n266: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n267: \n268: \n269: class PcapAnalyzer:\n270:     \"\"\"PCAP file analyzer using AgentCube Code Interpreter.\"\"\"\n271: \n272:     def __init__(\n273:         self,\n274:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n275:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n276:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n277:         verbose: bool = False,\n278:     ) -> None:\n279:         \"\"\"Initialize the PCAP analyzer.\n280: \n281:         Args:\n282:             router_url: Router URL (required, or set ROUTER_URL env var)\n283:             workload_manager_url: Workload Manager URL (optional)\n284:             auth_token: Authentication token (optional)\n285:             verbose: Enable verbose logging\n286:         \"\"\"\n287:         self.verbose = verbose\n288:         if verbose:\n289:             logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)\n290: \n291:         self.client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n292:             name=\"pcap-analyzer\",\n293:             namespace=\"default\",\n294:             ttl=3600,\n295:             router_url=router_url,\n296:             workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url,\n297:             auth_token=auth_token,\n298:             verbose=verbose,\n299:         )\n300: \n301:         self.remote_pcap_dir = \"/workspace/pcaps\"\n302:         self.remote_results_dir = \"/workspace/results\"\n303:         self.remote_analyzer_script = \"/workspace/analyzer.py\"\n304: \n305:     def setup_environment(self) -> None:\n306:         \"\"\"Set up the sandbox environment with required dependencies.\"\"\"\n307:         logger.info(\"Setting up sandbox environment...\")\n308: \n309:         # Create directories\n310:         self.client.execute_command(f\"mkdir -p {self.remote_pcap_dir}\")\n311:         self.client.execute_command(f\"mkdir -p {self.remote_results_dir}\")\n312: \n313:         # Install scapy\n314:         logger.info(\"Installing scapy...\")\n315:         result = self.client.execute_command(\n316:             \"pip install scapy --quiet\",\n317:             timeout=120.0,\n318:         )\n319:         logger.debug(f\"pip install output: {result}\")\n320: \n321:         logger.info(\"Environment setup complete\")\n322: \n323:     def upload_pcap(self, local_path: str) -> str:\n324:         \"\"\"Upload a PCAP file to the sandbox.\n325: \n326:         Args:\n327:             local_path: Local path to the PCAP file\n328: \n329:         Returns:\n330:             Remote path where the file was uploaded\n331:         \"\"\"\n332:         pcap_file = Path(local_path)\n333:         if not pcap_file.exists():\n334:             raise FileNotFoundError(f\"PCAP file not found: {local_path}\")\n335: \n336:         remote_path = f\"{self.remote_pcap_dir}/{pcap_file.name}\"\n337:         logger.info(f\"Uploading {local_path} to {remote_path}\")\n338: \n339:         self.client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)\n340: \n341:         # Verify upload\n342:         files = self.client.list_files(self.remote_pcap_dir)\n343:         logger.debug(f\"Files in remote directory: {files}\")\n344: \n345:         return remote_path\n346: \n347:     def create_analyzer_script(self) -> None:\n348:         \"\"\"Create the PCAP analysis script in the sandbox.\"\"\"\n349:         script_content = '''#!/usr/bin/env python3\n350: \"\"\"PCAP analysis script for AgentCube sandbox.\"\"\"\n351: \n352: import sys\n353: import json\n354: from pathlib import Path\n355: from scapy.all import rdpcap, IP, TCP, UDP, DNS, DNSQR, DNSRR\n356: \n357: \n358: def analyze_pcap(pcap_path: str) -> dict:\n359:     \"\"\"Analyze a PCAP file and return statistics.\n360: \n361:     Args:\n362:         pcap_path: Path to the PCAP file\n363: \n364:     Returns:\n365:         Dictionary containing analysis results\n366:     \"\"\"\n367:     try:\n368:         packets = rdpcap(pcap_path)\n369:     except Exception as e:\n370:         return {\"error\": f\"Failed to read PCAP: {str(e)}\"}\n371: \n372:     results = {\n373:         \"total_packets\": len(packets),\n374:         \"protocols\": {},\n375:         \"ip_summary\": {\"sources\": [], \"destinations\": []},\n376:         \"tcp_ports\": [],\n377:         \"udp_ports\": [],\n378:         \"dns_queries\": [],\n379:     }\n380: \n381:     source_ips = set()\n382:     dest_ips = set()\n383:     tcp_src_ports = set()\n384:     tcp_dst_ports = set()\n385:     udp_src_ports = set()\n386:     udp_dst_ports = set()\n387:     dns_queries_list = []\n388: \n389:     for pkt in packets:\n390:         # Protocol detection\n391:         if pkt.haslayer(IP):\n392:             source_ips.add(pkt[IP].src)\n393:             dest_ips.add(pkt[IP].dst)\n394: \n395:             if pkt.haslayer(TCP):\n396:                 proto_key = \"TCP\"\n397:                 tcp_src_ports.add(pkt[TCP].sport)\n398:                 tcp_dst_ports.add(pkt[TCP].dport)\n399:             elif pkt.haslayer(UDP):\n400:                 proto_key = \"UDP\"\n401:                 udp_src_ports.add(pkt[UDP].sport)\n402:                 udp_dst_ports.add(pkt[UDP].dport)\n403: \n404:                 if pkt.haslayer(DNS):\n405:                     dns_layer = pkt[DNS]\n406:                     if dns_layer.qd and dns_layer.qd.qname:\n407:                         dns_queries_list.append(\n408:                             dns_layer.qd.qname.decode() if isinstance(dns_layer.qd.qname, bytes)\n409:                             else str(dns_layer.qd.qname)\n410:                         )\n411:             else:\n412:                 proto_key = \"OTHER_IP\"\n413: \n414:             results[\"protocols\"][proto_key] = results[\"protocols\"].get(proto_key, 0) + 1\n415: \n416:     results[\"ip_summary\"][\"sources\"] = sorted(list(source_ips))\n417:     results[\"ip_summary\"][\"destinations\"] = sorted(list(dest_ips))\n418:     results[\"tcp_ports\"] = {\n419:         \"source_ports\": sorted(list(tcp_src_ports)),\n420:         \"destination_ports\": sorted(list(tcp_dst_ports)),\n421:     }\n422:     results[\"udp_ports\"] = {\n423:         \"source_ports\": sorted(list(udp_src_ports)),\n424:         \"destination_ports\": sorted(list(udp_dst_ports)),\n425:     }\n426:     results[\"dns_queries\"] = dns_queries_list\n427: \n428:     return results\n429: \n430: \n431: def main():\n432:     if len(sys.argv) < 3:\n433:         print(json.dumps({\"error\": \"Usage: analyzer.py <pcap_path> <output_path>\"}))\n434:         sys.exit(1)\n435: \n436:     pcap_path = sys.argv[1]\n437:     output_path = sys.argv[2]\n438: \n439:     results = analyze_pcap(pcap_path)\n440: \n441:     with open(output_path, \"w\") as f:\n442:         json.dump(results, f, indent=2)\n443: \n444:     print(json.dumps({\"status\": \"success\", \"output\": output_path}))\n445: \n446: \n447: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n448:     main()\n449: '''\n450: \n451:         logger.info(\"Creating analyzer script in sandbox...\")\n452:         self.client.write_file(script_content, self.remote_analyzer_script)\n453: \n454:     def analyze_pcap(self, remote_pcap_path: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n455:         \"\"\"Analyze a PCAP file in the sandbox.\n456: \n457:         Args:\n458:             remote_pcap_path: Remote path to the PCAP file\n459: \n460:         Returns:\n461:             Analysis results dictionary\n462:         \"\"\"\n463:         pcap_filename = Path(remote_pcap_path).stem\n464:         output_path = f\"{self.remote_results_dir}/{pcap_filename}_analysis.json\"\n465: \n466:         logger.info(f\"Analyzing PCAP: {remote_pcap_path}\")\n467: \n468:         try:\n469:             # Run the analyzer script\n470:             result = self.client.run_code(\n471:                 language=\"python\",\n472:                 code=f\"\"\"\n473: import sys\n474: sys.path.insert(0, '/workspace')\n475: exec(open('{self.remote_analyzer_script}').read())\n476: \n477: import sys\n478: sys.argv = ['analyzer.py', '{remote_pcap_path}', '{output_path}']\n479: main()\n480: \"\"\",\n481:                 timeout=60.0,\n482:             )\n483: \n484:             logger.debug(f\"Analysis output: {result}\")\n485: \n486:             # Download results\n487:             logger.info(f\"Downloading results from {output_path}\")\n488:             local_results_path = f\"/tmp/{pcap_filename}_analysis.json\"\n489:             self.client.download_file(output_path, local_results_path)\n490: \n491:             # Read results\n492:             with open(local_results_path, \"r\") as f:\n493:                 results = json.load(f)\n494: \n495:             return results\n496: \n497:         except CommandExecutionError as e:\n498:             logger.error(f\"Command execution failed: {e.stderr}\")\n499:             raise\n500:         except Exception as e:\n501:             logger.error(f\"Analysis failed: {e}\")\n502:             raise DataPlaneError(f\"PCAP analysis failed: {e}\")\n503: \n504:     def close(self) -> None:\n505:         \"\"\"Close the client and cleanup resources.\"\"\"\n506:         logger.info(\"Closing connection...\")\n507:         self.client.stop()\n508: \n509: \n510: def main() -> None:\n511:     \"\"\"Main entry point for the PCAP analyzer example.\"\"\"\n512:     import argparse\n513: \n514:     parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n515:         description=\"PCAP Analyzer Example for AgentCube Python SDK\",\n516:         formatter_class=argparse.RawDescriptionHelpFormatter,\n517:         epilog=\"\"\"\n518: Examples:\n519:     # Analyze a PCAP file\n520:     python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap\n521: \n522:     # Analyze with verbose output\n523:     python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/dns_queries.pcap -v\n524: \n525:     # Use custom router URL\n526:     python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap --router-url http://localhost:8080\n527: \"\"\",\n528:     )\n529: \n530:     parser.add_argument(\n531:         \"pcap_file\",\n532:         nargs=\"?\",\n533:         default=\"test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap\",\n534:         help=\"Path to the PCAP file to analyze (default: test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap)\",\n535:     )\n536:     parser.add_argument(\n537:         \"--router-url\",\n538:         type=str,\n539:         default=None,\n540:         help=\"Router URL (overrides ROUTER_URL env var)\",\n541:     )\n542:     parser.add_argument(\n543:         \"--workload-manager-url\",\n544:         type=str,\n545:         default=None,\n546:         help=\"Workload Manager URL (overrides WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var)\",\n547:     )\n548:     parser.add_argument(\n549:         \"--auth-token\",\n550:         type=str,\n551:         default=None,\n552:         help=\"Authentication token (overrides SA token file)\",\n553:     )\n554:     parser.add_argument(\n555:         \"-v\",\n556:         \"--verbose\",\n557:         action=\"store_true\",\n558:         help=\"Enable verbose logging\",\n559:     )\n560:     parser.add_argument(\n561:         \"--generate-samples\",\n562:         action=\"store_true\",\n563:         help=\"Generate sample PCAP files before analyzing\",\n564:     )\n565: \n566:     args = parser.parse_args()\n567: \n568:     # Generate sample PCAPs if requested\n569:     if args.generate_samples:\n570:         logger.info(\"Generating sample PCAP files...\")\n571:         from sample_pcap import main as generate_samples\n572:         generate_samples()\n573: \n574:     # Validate PCAP file exists\n575:     pcap_path = Path(args.pcap_file)\n576:     if not pcap_path.exists():\n577:         logger.error(f\"PCAP file not found: {args.pcap_file}\")\n578:         logger.info(\"Use --generate-samples to create sample PCAP files\")\n579:         sys.exit(1)\n580: \n581:     # Initialize analyzer\n582:     analyzer = PcapAnalyzer(\n583:         router_url=args.router_url,\n584:         workload_manager_url=args.workload_manager_url,\n585:         auth_token=args.auth_token,\n586:         verbose=args.verbose,\n587:     )\n588: \n589:     try:\n590:         # Setup environment\n591:         analyzer.setup_environment()\n592: \n593:         # Create analyzer script\n594:         analyzer.create_analyzer_script()\n595: \n596:         # Upload PCAP\n597:         remote_pcap_path = analyzer.upload_pcap(str(pcap_path))\n598: \n599:         # Analyze PCAP\n600:         results = analyzer.analyze_pcap(remote_pcap_path)\n601: \n602:         # Display results\n603:         print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 60)\n604:         print(\"PCAP ANALYSIS RESULTS\")\n605:         print(\"=\" * 60)\n606:         print(json.dumps(results, indent=2))\n607:         print(\"=\" * 60)\n608: \n609:     except FileNotFoundError as e:\n610:         logger.error(f\"File error: {e}\")\n611:         sys.exit(1)\n612:     except CommandExecutionError as e:\n613:         logger.error(f\"Command failed (exit {e.exit_code}): {e.stderr}\")\n614:         sys.exit(1)\n615:     except DataPlaneError as e:\n616:         logger.error(f\"Data plane error: {e}\")\n617:         sys.exit(1)\n618:     except Exception as e:\n619:         logger.error(f\"Unexpected error: {e}\")\n620:         sys.exit(1)\n621:     finally:\n622:         analyzer.close()\n623: \n624: \n625: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n626:     main()\n627: ```\n628: \n629: ### 5. README 文档 (README.md)\n630: \n631: ```markdown\n632: # PCAP Analyzer Example\n633: \n634: This example demonstrates how to use the AgentCube Python SDK's `CodeInterpreterClient` to analyze PCAP (packet capture) files in a sandbox environment.\n635: \n636: ## Features\n637: \n638: - Upload PCAP files to sandbox\n639: - Install Python dependencies (scapy) in sandbox\n640: - Analyze network traffic:\n641:   - Protocol distribution (TCP/UDP/OTHER)\n642:   - IP address summary (sources and destinations)\n643:   - TCP/UDP port analysis\n644:   - DNS query extraction\n645: - Download analysis results as JSON\n646: \n647: ## Prerequisites\n648: \n649: - Python 3.10+\n650: - AgentCube Python SDK installed (`pip install -e ..`)\n651: - Router URL (via `ROUTER_URL` environment variable or `--router-url` argument)\n652: - Optional: Workload Manager URL and auth token for K8s clusters\n653: \n654: ## Installation\n655: \n656: 1. Install example dependencies:\n657: \n658: ```bash\n659: pip install -r requirements.txt\n660: ```\n661: \n662: 2. Generate sample PCAP files (optional):\n663: \n664: ```bash\n665: python sample_pcap.py\n666: ```\n667: \n668: ## Usage\n669: \n670: ### Basic Example\n671: \n672: Analyze a sample PCAP file:\n673: \n674: ```bash\n675: python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap\n676: ```\n677: \n678: ### With Verbose Output\n679: \n680: Enable debug logging:\n681: \n682: ```bash\n683: python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/dns_queries.pcap -v\n684: ```\n685: \n686: ### Custom Router URL\n687: \n688: Specify router URL explicitly:\n689: \n690: ```bash\n691: python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap --router-url http://localhost:8080\n692: ```\n693: \n694: ### Generate and Analyze\n695: \n696: Generate sample PCAPs and analyze in one step:\n697: \n698: ```bash\n699: python pcap_analyzer.py --generate-samples\n700: ```\n701: \n702: ## Example Output\n703: \n704: ```json\n705: {\n706:   \"total_packets\": 2,\n707:   \"protocols\": {\n708:     \"TCP\": 2\n709:   },\n710:   \"ip_summary\": {\n711:     \"sources\": [\"192.168.1.100\", \"93.184.216.34\"],\n712:     \"destinations\": [\"192.168.1.100\", \"93.184.216.34\"]\n713:   },\n714:   \"tcp_ports\": {\n715:     \"source_ports\": [80, 54321],\n716:     \"destination_ports\": [80, 54321]\n717:   },\n718:   \"udp_ports\": {\n719:     \"source_ports\": [],\n720:     \"destination_ports\": []\n721:   },\n722:   \"dns_queries\": []\n723: }\n724: ```\n725: \n726: ## How It Works\n727: \n728: 1. **Environment Setup**: Creates directories and installs `scapy` in the sandbox\n729: 2. **File Upload**: Uploads the PCAP file to `/workspace/pcaps/`\n730: 3. **Script Creation**: Writes the analyzer script to `/workspace/analyzer.py`\n731: 4. **Code Execution**: Runs the analyzer using `run_code()`\n732: 5. **Result Download**: Downloads JSON results from `/workspace/results/`\n733: 6. **Cleanup**: Closes the session and deletes resources\n734: \n735: ## Code Structure\n736: \n737: - `pcap_analyzer.py` - Main example script with `PcapAnalyzer` class\n738: - `sample_pcap.py` - Generates sample PCAP files for testing\n739: - `test_pcaps/` - Directory containing sample PCAP files\n740:   - `basic_http.pcap` - HTTP traffic example\n741:   - `dns_queries.pcap` - DNS queries example\n742: \n743: ## Error Handling\n744: \n745: The example handles common errors:\n746: \n747: - `FileNotFoundError` - PCAP file doesn't exist\n748: - `CommandExecutionError` - Command fails in sandbox (non-zero exit)\n749: - `DataPlaneError` - Data plane communication errors\n750: - Generic exceptions with proper logging\n751: \n752: ## Advanced Usage\n753: \n754: ### Using as a Module\n755: \n756: You can import and use the `PcapAnalyzer` class in your own code:\n757: \n758: ```python\n759: from pcap_analyzer import PcapAnalyzer\n760: \n761: analyzer = PcapAnalyzer(\n762:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n763:     verbose=True\n764: )\n765: \n766: try:\n767:     analyzer.setup_environment()\n768:     remote_path = analyzer.upload_pcap(\"my_capture.pcap\")\n769:     results = analyzer.analyze_pcap(remote_path)\n770:     print(results)\n771: finally:\n772:     analyzer.close()\n773: ```\n774: \n775: ### Custom Analysis\n776: \n777: Modify the analyzer script in `create_analyzer_script()` to perform custom analysis:\n778: \n779: - Extract HTTP payloads\n780: - Analyze TLS/SSL handshakes\n781: - Detect specific protocols\n782: - Generate visualizations\n783: \n784: ## Troubleshooting\n785: \n786: ### Router URL Not Set\n787: \n788: ```\n789: ValueError: Router URL must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL\n790: ```\n791: \n792: **Solution**: Set `ROUTER_URL` environment variable or use `--router-url` argument.\n793: \n794: ### Session Creation Failed\n795: \n796: ```\n797: SessionError: Failed to create session\n798: ```\n799: \n800: **Solution**: Check Workload Manager URL and auth token configuration.\n801: \n802: ### Command Timeout\n803: \n804: ```\n805: CommandExecutionError: Command failed (exit 124): timeout\n806: ```\n807: \n808: **Solution**: Increase timeout parameter or optimize analysis script.\n809: \n810: ## Related Documentation\n811: \n812: - [AgentCube Python SDK Design](../../design.md)\n813: - [AgentCube Python SDK Spec](../../spec.md)\n814: - [CodeInterpreterClient API](../../agentcube/code_interpreter.py)\n815: \n816: ## License\n817: \n818: Same as AgentCube project license.\n819: ```\n820: \n821: ### 6. 示例依赖 (requirements.txt)\n822: \n823: ```txt\n824: # PCAP Analyzer Example Dependencies\n825: scapy>=2.5.0\n826: ```\n827: \n828: ## Impact Analysis\n829: \n830: ### 依赖影响\n831: \n832: | 依赖项 | 版本 | 用途 |\n833: |--------|------|------|\n834: | `scapy` | >=2.5.0 | PCAP 文件解析和分析 |\n835: | `agentcube-sdk` | latest | AgentCube Python SDK |\n836: \n837: ### 模块依赖关系\n838: \n839: ```\n840: sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/\n841: ├── pcap_analyzer.py          # 依赖：agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient\n842: ├── sample_pcap.py            # 依赖：scapy\n843: ├── requirements.txt          # 示例依赖\n844: ├── README.md                 # 文档\n845: └── test_pcaps/\n846:     ├── basic_http.pcap       # 测试数据\n847:     └── dns_queries.pcap      # 测试数据\n848: ```\n849: \n850: ### 向后兼容性\n851: \n852: - 示例应用，不影响现有 API\n853: - 独立运行，不修改 SDK 核心代码\n854: - 测试数据可重新生成\n855: \n856: ### 测试影响\n857: \n858: - 需测试完整流程（上传→分析→下载）\n859: - 需测试错误场景（文件不存在、超时等）\n860: - 需验证分析结果准确性\n861: \n862: ### 性能影响\n863: \n864: - PCAP 文件大小影响上传时间\n865: - 沙箱中 pip install 需要额外时间（约 10-20 秒）\n866: - 分析复杂度影响执行时间\n867: \n868: ## Alternatives Considered\n869: \n870: ### 方案 1: 使用 dpkt 替代 scapy\n871: \n872: **优点:**\n873: - 更轻量级\n874: - 解析速度更快\n875: \n876: **缺点:**\n877: - API 较复杂\n878: - 功能不如 scapy 丰富\n879: \n880: **决策:** 选择 `scapy`，提供更友好的 API 和更丰富的功能。\n881: \n882: ### 方案 2: 本地预处理 PCAP 文件\n883: \n884: **优点:**\n885: - 减少沙箱计算负担\n886: - 可以预处理大文件\n887: \n888: **缺点:**\n889: - 增加本地依赖\n890: - 不符合示例目的（展示沙箱能力）\n891: \n892: **决策:** 在沙箱中完成全部分析，展示 Code Interpreter 能力。\n893: \n894: ### 方案 3: 多文件分析示例\n895: \n896: **优点:**\n897: - 展示批量处理能力\n898: - 更实用\n899: \n900: **缺点:**\n901: - 示例复杂度增加\n902: - 不适合作为基础示例\n903: \n904: **决策:** 首期实现单文件分析，后续可扩展为批量分析示例。\n905: \n906: ### 方案 4: 使用 tshark/tcpdump\n907: \n908: **优点:**\n909: - 专业工具，功能强大\n910: - 支持更多协议\n911: \n912: **缺点:**\n913: - 需要预装工具\n914: - 输出格式复杂，解析困难\n915: \n916: **决策:** 使用 Python + scapy，纯 Python 方案更易理解和扩展。\n917: \n918: ## Testing Strategy\n919: \n920: ### 单元测试\n921: \n922: 1. **样本生成测试** - 验证 `sample_pcap.py` 生成有效 PCAP 文件\n923: 2. **脚本创建测试** - 验证分析脚本正确写入沙箱\n924: 3. **结果解析测试** - 验证 JSON 结果格式正确\n925: \n926: ### 集成测试\n927: \n928: 1. **完整流程测试** - 上传→分析→下载全流程\n929: 2. **错误处理测试** - 文件不存在、超时等场景\n930: 3. **环境变量测试** - 不同配置下的行为\n931: \n932: ### 验证标准\n933: \n934: 1. **功能性**:\n935:    - [ ] 能成功上传 PCAP 文件\n936:    - [ ] 能正确安装 scapy\n937:    - [ ] 能正确分析 PCAP 文件\n938:    - [ ] 能正确下载分析结果\n939: \n940: 2. **准确性**:\n941:    - [ ] 协议统计正确\n942:    - [ ] IP 地址提取正确\n943:    - [ ] 端口信息正确\n944:    - [ ] DNS 查询提取正确\n945: \n946: 3. **错误处理**:\n947:    - [ ] 文件不存在时抛出 `FileNotFoundError`\n948:    - [ ] 命令失败时抛出 `CommandExecutionError`\n949:    - [ ] 超时时正确处理\n950: \n951: ## Acceptance Criteria\n952: \n953: - [ ] `pcap_analyzer.py` 可独立运行\n954: - [ ] `sample_pcap.py` 生成有效的 PCAP 文件\n955: - [ ] 示例能正确分析 HTTP 流量 PCAP\n956: - [ ] 示例能正确分析 DNS 查询 PCAP\n957: - [ ] 分析结果 JSON 格式正确\n958: - [ ] README 文档完整（Usage、Examples、Troubleshooting）\n959: - [ ] 错误处理完善（文件不存在、超时、网络错误）\n960: - [ ] 代码符合 Python 风格规范（PEP 8）\n961: - [ ] 日志输出清晰有用\n962: - [ ] 支持 `-v` 详细日志模式\n963: - [ ] 支持 `--generate-samples` 一键生成并分析\n964: - [ ] 支持 `--router-url` 等参数覆盖环境变量\n965: \n966: ## Dependencies\n967: \n968: ### 必需依赖\n969: - AgentCube Python SDK\n970: - Router 服务运行中\n971: - `scapy` 库（示例依赖）\n972: \n973: ### 可选依赖\n974: - Workload Manager（用于创建 session）\n975: - Kubernetes 集群（用于 SA token 认证）\n976: \n977: ### 被依赖\n978: - AR-028/AR-029 (SDK HTTP 底层客户端) - 提供 `CodeInterpreterClient`\n979: - `sdk-python/design.md` - SDK 设计规范\n980: - `sdk-python/spec.md` - SDK 规范\n981: \n982: ## Migration Notes\n983: \n984: ### 从零到示例\n985: \n986: 1. **创建目录结构**\n987:    ```bash\n988:    mkdir -p sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/test_pcaps\n989:    ```\n990: \n991: 2. **复制示例文件**\n992:    - 复制 `pcap_analyzer.py`\n993:    - 复制 `sample_pcap.py`\n994:    - 复制 `requirements.txt`\n995:    - 复制 `README.md`\n996: \n997: 3. **生成测试数据**\n998:    ```bash\n999:    cd sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer\n1000:    python sample_pcap.py\n1001:    ```\n1002: \n1003: 4. **运行示例**\n1004:    ```bash\n1005:    python pcap_analyzer.py --generate-samples\n1006:    ```\n1007: \n1008: ### 破坏性变更\n1009: 无 - 新增示例，不影响现有代码。\n1010: \n1011: ### 行为变更\n1012: 无 - 示例应用，不影响 SDK 行为。\n1013: \n1014: ## Open Questions\n1015: \n1016: 1. 是否需要支持更多 PCAP 分析功能（如 HTTP 内容提取）？\n1017: 2. 是否需要添加可视化输出（如协议分布图）？\n1018: 3. 是否需要支持批量 PCAP 文件分析？\n1019: 4. 是否需要添加更多示例 PCAP 文件（如 TLS 流量）？\n1020: 5. 是否需要集成到 CI/CD 的示例测试中？\n1021: \n1022: ## References\n1023: \n1024: - `sdk-python/design.md` - SDK 设计规范\n1025: - `sdk-python/spec.md` - SDK 规范\n1026: - `sdk-python/examples/basic_usage.py` - 基础用法示例\n1027: - `sdk-python/examples/agent_runtime_usage.py` - Agent Runtime 示例\n1028: - Scapy Documentation: https://scapy.readthedocs.io/\n1029: - PCAP file format: https://wiki.wireshark.org/Development/LibpcapFileFormat\n\n(End of file - total 1029 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用\n\n## Purpose\n\n本提案实现 AgentCube Python SDK 的 PCAP 分析器示例应用，展示如何使用 `CodeInterpreterClient` 在沙箱中执行网络数据包分析任务。该示例是 AgentCube SDK 的官方示例应用，帮助用户理解如何使用 Code Interpreter 进行文件处理、代码执行和结果获取。\n\n目标是：\n\n1. **SDK 使用示范** - 展示 `CodeInterpreterClient` 的完整使用流程\n2. **PCAP 分析场景** - 演示如何上传、解析、分析网络数据包文件\n3. **最佳实践** - 提供文件操作、代码执行、错误处理的最佳实践示例\n4. **可运行示例** - 提供完整的、可独立运行的示例代码和测试数据\n\n本提案基于 Python SDK design.md 和 spec.md 实现，遵循 AgentCube 示例应用规范。\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** example  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-037/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775887718871,"end":1775887718904}}}}
